        "section": "",
        "section_color": "",
        "section_duration": 0,
        "is_substep": false,
        "step": "Take aliquot of beads out of refrigerator and allow to warm to room temperature.",
        "data": null,
        "protocol_id": 37637,
        "case_id": 0,
        "critical_ids": "",
        "duration": 0,
        "original_id": 0,
        "number": "1",
        "cases": [],
        "critical": null
      },
      {
        "id": 1181066,
        "guid": "42463CF0B77811EBB5C4C3FAE405C4D8",
        "previous_id": 1181129,
        "previous_guid": "F73EC9C0B78611EB9D2639A445D24D41",
        "section": "",
        "section_color": "",
        "section_duration": 0,
        "is_substep": false,
        "step": "Prepare fresh 70% EtOH. \n\nFrom the Agencourt XP beads manual: &#34;Fresh 70% ethanol should be prepared for optimal results. There is also miscibility involved with ethanol and water. For example, measuring out 70 mL of ethanol and topping off to 100 mL with water will generate ~65% ethanol. Measuring 70 mL ethanol and 30 mL water separately, then combining them will generate ~95 mL of 70% ethanol.&#34;",
        "data": null,
        "protocol_id": 37637,
        "case_id": 0,
        "critical_ids": "",
        "duration": 0,
        "original_id": 0,
        "number": "4",
        "cases": [],
        "critical": null
      },
      {
        "id": 1181068,
        "guid": "B69A34D0B77811EBB5C4C3FAE405C4D8",
        "previous_id": 1181065,
        "previous_guid": "122F7270B77811EBB5C4C3FAE405C4D8",
        "section": "",
        "section_color": "",
        "section_duration": 0,
        "is_substep": false,
        "step": "Start program and input the numer of samples you have. It will then tell you the minimum volumes for each reagent. The positions in the reservoir rack are:\n1. Molecular grade H2O\n3. Beads\n5. 70% EtOH\n7. Elution buffer (e.g. H2O, TRIS-Acetate (10 mM pH 8.0), or TE Buffer (10 mM Tris-Acetate pH 8.0, 1 mM EDTA))\n\nYou can use the level sensor to detect volumes or measure them with a serological pipette. Do not start the program until all of your items are in the correct positions.",
        "data": null,
        "protocol_id": 37637,
        "case_id": 0,
        "critical_ids": "",
        "duration": 0,
        "original_id": 0,
        "number": "2",
        "cases": [],
        "critical": null
      },
      {
        "id": 1181086,
        "guid": "06DFB770B77A11EBB5C4C3FAE405C4D8",
        "previous_id": 1181066,
        "previous_guid": "42463CF0B77811EBB5C4C3FAE405C4D8",
        "section": "",
        "section_color": "",
        "section_duration": 0,
        "is_substep": false,
        "step": "Place reagents, your PCR plate, and a new clean plate on the epMotion. \n\nMaterials layout:\n[bead cleanup position.png]](https://content.protocols.io/files/jm7685be.jpg)\n \n\n\nRun the program. It will take approximately 1 hour for a full plate.",
        "data": null,
        "protocol_id": 37637,
        "case_id": 0,
        "critical_ids": "",
        "duration": 0,
        "original_id": 0,
        "number": "5",
        "cases": [],
